<br>
Anyone have that &quot;Out of System Resources&quot; error in WinME, even though you have like 384MB of RAM or whatever?<br>
<br>
Try this:<br>
Start--Settings--Control Panel  (Or WIN+BREAK on the keyboard)<br>
Go to performance, file system, troubleshooting.  DISABLE System Restore.<br>
<br>
It helped alot.  It hasn't been proven, but it *seems* to be the main reason for most of those &quot;out of resources&quot; messages.  It apparently wastes a lot of time and resources backing up *every* file you make a change to or even &quot;touch&quot; (bad news if you like to do Digital Video editing, where it makes copies of all your  2GB files). <br>
<br>
To Bobbins' reply:<br>
If you find a way to downgrade to Win98SE by installing it on top of WinME, I'd be most interested :)  Foolishly, I upgraded to W.ME when it first came out, thinking they'd shown a good example with 98SE and couldn't possibly get it wrong this time :)<br>
I can't just go formatting it to install 98 though, I have a lot of stuff on there and it'd take months to find it all again :p <p>-- <br>
