That Win-Break keystroke is pretty nifty, though :) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utudamorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tudamorf</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://lag999.homestead.com/files/biggrin.gif width=15 height=15 BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/30/01 8:23:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneralot.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1108.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://lag999.homestead.com/files/rtfm.gif width=100 height=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: There are very few things slower than Windows.</span><hr size=1> Windows ME is Micro$oft's biggest disaster since DOS 4.0 (anyone remember how badly they messed that up?).  If you don't want to buy Win2K (good OS!), go for Win98SE.  98SE is actually a pretty stable, somewhat mature OS and has the best gaming compatibility and overall software support.  Plus, I think it's cheaper than ME.<br>
<br>
Of course if you're an MS-hating Unix geek you could always use Linux.  Very stable and feature-filled, except half of your hardware and none of your apps will run on it, and you'll have to spend 3 months just getting through the setup stage.  ;) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucloudanetrihart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cloudane Trihart</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://wwp.icq.com/scripts/online.dll?icq=25869912&img=5 BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/30/01 4:09:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneralot.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1108.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: There are very few things slower than Windows.</span><hr size=1> I'm using Slackware Linux as we speak :)  I'd been trying various forms of Linux on and off for a fair few years, always finding little niggles and going back, until I finally found my perfect distro :) <br>
It became my primary OS the moment Steve Ballmer started calling it &quot;a cancer&quot;...  from then on, it became a matter of principle to use MS products as little as possible :p<br>
<br>
There are still two things I use Windows for though:<br>
1) Everquest<br>
2) Video editing<br>
<br>
You can't really beat Win9x or a Mac when it comes to video editing software (Adobe Premiere comes to mind).   The existing free tools just don't cut it.<br>
<br>
Oh yeah, and I have Win95, Win98, Win98SE, WinME and Win2000... I always was a sucker for Microsoft's marketing :(  Not any more though, I'd sooner dust off my Amiga 500 than be forced to use Windows XP!<br>
<br>
Upgrading to 2K isn't such a bad idea actually.  I think there were a few programs that wouldn't work on it last time I tried, but they've had plenty of time to be upgraded. <p>-- <br>
