<br>
I have a 20gig drive paritioned into 2 10gig drives.  Every other month or so, I simply re-format the C drive.  Since I have all of the driver upgrades and stuff on the D drive, formatting is actually fairly painless since all the only things I lose would be the stuff I had the CD to begin with.  <br>
<br>
Just make sure you copy your email and bookmarks over to the D drive :)<br>
<br>
Borras<br>
