<br>
I've also got an image of my windows drive lying around somewhere... I can just copy that over when things start getting messy :)<br>
<br>
Of course, if Windows did a better job keeping track of itself, all this wouldn't be necessary... :/   Tudamorf, is Win2k better about that sort of thing? (I'm assuming it must be, from all the good things I've heard about it. but I'm curious about how much better :) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utudamorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tudamorf</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://lag999.homestead.com/files/biggrin.gif width=15 height=15 BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/1/01 12:27:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneralot.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1108.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://lag999.homestead.com/files/rtfm.gif width=100 height=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: There are very few things slower than Windows.</span><hr size=1> <b><i>Tudamorf, is Win2k better about that sort of thing? (I'm assuming it must be, from all the good things I've heard about it. but I'm curious about how much better :) </b></i><br>
<br>
I'm no Win2K guru, but from the looks of it, doesn't seem to me like it's very different.  Still can get messy when you install/uninstall lots of stuff, although Win2K does a much better job of suppressing old drivers when you swap hardware.  In many cases it automatically deactivated the old hardware, installed the new hardware *without a restart*, and popped me right in ... then when I put back my old hardware, it automatically deactivated the new stuff and reactivated the old stuff.  Considering the types of drivers and quantity of stuff I swap in and out, in Win98SE it would have been a total nightmare ("you have moved your mouse 2 cm ... restart please ... you moved another 2cm ... restart please, GPF invalid VxD, blablabla"). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubobbinsrumblebelly.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bobbins Rumblebelly</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://rcloues.home.mindspring.com/images/smiley.gif width=21 height=21 BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/1/01 1:31:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneralot.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1108.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://rcloues.home.mindspring.com/images/colorsmilies2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: There are very few things slower than Windows.</span><hr size=1> That's pretty cool.  I'm usually pretty careful about uninstalling drivers before reinstalling them, but occasionally I make mistakes and they can be a nightmare to clean up after (booting to safe mode, cleaning out the old driver files, and then searching the registry if needed... bleh).<br>
<br>
Ah, GPF's... the thing MS supposedly did away with (by renaming them, heh).  I don't know how, but I managed to create one of those a few days ago.  I was doing something when everything slowed down and stopped dead.  It didn't seem too out of place, since I crash once or twice every day, anyway.  But then I mashed ctrl-alt-delete, in the hopes of killing whatever program had so offended my poor computer... and up popped a white dialog box that kindly told me, "General Protection Fault!"  Ah, the memories... haven't seen that box in years :) <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneralot.showPrevMessage?topicID=1108.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneralot.showNextMessage?topicID=1108.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneralot.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1108.topic&index=8><img src=http://dev.thedruidsgrove.org/images/forum/addreplya.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneralot.emailToFriend?topicID=1108.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneralot.threadControl?topicID=1108.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneralot.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1108.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneralot.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1108.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of rep